suites.title: Basic existence and idle state checks

specs.title: page defines the expected functions and idle state does no DOM modifications
appendElement calls denoteElement and appends the element to #deque
appendElement does not mutate internal deque array (edge case verifying implementation)
appendElement with null/undefined values results in stringified insertion into #deque
dequeue removes and returns the first element of window.deque
dequeue on an empty deque returns undefined (edge case)
displayArray outputs concatenated elements followed by a newline to #array
displayArray on empty deque appends only a newline character to #array
calling displayArray when #array is missing throws (ERROR trigger / edge case)
removeElement denotes the targeted element then denotes null (per implementation)
removeElement with out-of-bounds index denotes undefined then null (edge case due to implementation override)
denoteElement appends the provided element string representation to #deque
denoteElement with falsy values appends their string equivalents
simulate all FSM events by invoking the corresponding functions / behaviors
